read

String read()
            throws IOException
Reads an molecule entry as (unparsed) String representation.

Parameters:
mol - the molecule to store the data
Returns:
null if the reader contains no more relevant data. Otherwise the String representation of the whole molecule entry is returned.
Throws:
IOException - typical IOException

read

boolean read(Molecule mol)
             throws IOException,
                    MoleculeIOException
Reads an molecule entry from the initialized molecule reader. If an MoleculeIOException occurs the molecule reader stream should be set to the start of the next molecule entry. Use: skipReaderEntry()

Parameters:
mol - the molecule to store the data
Returns:
false if the reader contains no more relevant data. true if a molecule was succesfull readed. If the molecule is incorrect or can't be parsed use MoleculeIOException.
Throws:
IOException - typical IOException
MoleculeIOException - If an serious molecule parsing error occured. This is important to skip molecule entries.

read

boolean read(Molecule mol,
             String title)
             throws IOException,
                    MoleculeIOException
Reads an molecule entry from the initialized molecule reader. If an MoleculeIOException occurs the molecule reader stream should be set to the start of the next molecule entry. Use: skipReaderEntry()

Parameters:
mol - the molecule to store the data
title - the title of the molecule. If title==null the title entry from the molecule mol.getTitle() should be used
Returns:
false if the reader contains no more relevant data. true if a molecule was succesfull readed. If the molecule is incorrect or can't be parsed use MoleculeIOException.
Throws:
IOException - typical IOException
MoleculeIOException - If an serious molecule parsing error occured. This is important to skip molecule entries.

skipReaderEntry

boolean skipReaderEntry()
                        throws IOException
Skips an molecule or the rest of a molecule entry to grant the next read(Molecule mol) invocation a proper starting position. This method should always be called if you plan to throw an MoleculeIOException.

Returns:
Description of the Return Value
